Cute little French place with tiny-tiny tables :) they don't take reservations, so you might need to wait in line for a bit to get a table for brunch.
Everything we ordered came out nice, though the portions were quite small. Great service, loved my cappuccino and chocolate mousse was yummy!

originalText.text:
Buvette: Where French Toast Dreams Come True (and the Line is Worth It!)

Forget everything you think you know about French toast. Buvette's version is a revelation - fluffy, golden pillows soaked in a delicate vanilla custard, then dusted with the perfect amount of condensed milk ü§§ It's the kind of dish that makes you want to sigh with contentment and maybe even shed a happy tear (FOR REAL!).

But the magic doesn't stop there. The entire brunch menu at Buvette is a symphony of fresh, seasonal ingredients and perfectly executed dishes.

Just be prepared for a little wait. Buvette is a New York City institution, and there's usually a line snaking out the door. But trust me, it's worth every minute!!! The charming atmosphere, friendly service, and, of course, the incredible food will have you coming back for more in no time.

Here's what makes Buvette a 5-star brunch destination:

- French toast that's pure perfection: Seriously, it's the best I've ever had.
- Outstanding brunch menu: Everything from the savory to the sweet is top-notch.
- Charming atmosphere: Buvette has a warm and inviting vibe that feels quintessentially Parisian.
- Friendly service: The staff is attentive and helpful, even when they're slammed.

So, if you're looking for a truly unforgettable brunch experience, head to Buvette. Just be prepared to wait, and savor every delicious bite when you finally get your table.
